    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FAYETTEVILLE, Ark.\n\u2013 Northern Colorado struck first but couldn't hold off a late push from No. four Arkansas, falling 13\u20132 as the Razorbacks pulled away in the final innings.\nThe Bears came out aggressive in the top of the first, as\nBrett Barber\nand\nJaden Stone\nreached base and created early pressure. A throwing error allowed Barber to score the game's first run, and\nEaston Bryant\nfollowed with an RBI single to give UNC a 2\u20130 lead.\nArkansas responded in the bottom half of the inning with a lead off home run from Damian Ruiz and went on to even the score before the frame ended. The Razorbacks carried that momentum into the second inning, taking a 3\u20132 lead, and added two more runs in the third to stretch the advantage to 5\u20132.\nNorthern Colorado threatened in several innings but couldn't capitalize.\nMason Griffin\nrecorded a lead off single in the second, and the Bears put runners aboard in both the third and sixth but were unable to bring them home. After a stretch of scoreless innings, Arkansas broke the game open in the seventh. A solo home run from TJ Pompey ignited a four-run frame, with the Razorbacks using walks, a double and a passed ball to extend the lead to 9\u20132.\nArkansas added four more runs in the eighth, combining timely hits with additional free passes to seal the 13\u20132 result.\nON DECK:\nNorthern Colorado looks to bounce back in game two of the midweek series against the Razorbacks. First pitch is set for 2 p.m. MDT at Baum-Walker Stadium.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball)."
